ue since it affects how the content is presented, even though the underlying information remains intelligible. I'm verifying all six configuration properties are documented in s3, and both code examples are present. The main issue I've found is the RST markup leak in s1, which is minor. The numbering in s2's return processing section reuses \"4.\" from the inbound flow, but since they're in separate subsections, it's not technically incorrect.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19665,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19665,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c44f6b09-34b6-4d8c-8018-fcfe21e80a12","uuid":"e71d227f-b559-4332-8852-1aa50439d572"}
